### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

### Signup - Register New User
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Verify OTP (Use OTP from console)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "otp": "123456"
}

### Login
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Forgot Password
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Reset Password (Use OTP from console)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "otp": "123456",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123"
}

### Resend OTP
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/resend-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}


### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### QR ENDPOINTS (requires Bearer token)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### Create QR - WhatsApp type
POST http://localhost:5000/api/qr
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "name": "My WhatsApp QR",
  "type": "whatsapp",
  "whatsappData": {
    "name": "John Doe",
    "message": "Hello! I scanned your QR code."
  }
}

### Create QR - Website type
POST http://localhost:5000/api/qr
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "name": "My Website QR",
  "type": "website",
  "websiteData": {
    "url": "https://example.com"
  }
}

### Get All QRs
GET http://localhost:5000/api/qr
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### Get QR by ID
GET http://localhost:5000/api/qr/QR_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### Update QR
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/qr/QR_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Updated QR Name",
  "whatsappData": {
    "name": "Jane Doe",
    "message": "Updated message"
  }
}

### Delete QR
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/qr/QR_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

### Increment Scan Count (Public - called when QR is scanned)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/qr/QR_ID_HERE/scan
